- 190 seconds?

150
00:07:31,369 --> 00:07:32,454
Let's do it.

151
00:07:32,537 --> 00:07:35,040
What-What's going on?
What's happening with the bar?

152
00:07:35,123 --> 00:07:38,168
The bar is, uh, harrowing at the moment.

153
00:07:38,251 --> 00:07:42,172
I'm working under Omar,
which has been character-building.

154
00:07:42,756 --> 00:07:47,552
- It is fucked up, honestly.
- [sighs] He makes these, like, insane beers. They all have, like, a hook to them.

155
00:07:47,636 --> 00:07:52,182
- A hook? What do you mean?
- Yeah, like, uh, - Cinnamon Toast stout. - Oh, dear.

156
00:07:52,265 --> 00:07:57,854
- Like, Count Chocula IPA. Shit like that.
- [laughs] Oh, that sounds good?

157
00:07:57,938 --> 00:08:02,108
- No. I mean, it's gross.
- [chuckles] You'd probably like it though. It's very sweet and sugary.

158
00:08:02,192 --> 00:08:03,777
[chuckles, sighs]

159
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:06,570
You'll never guess who I actually got
a job offer from the other day.

160
00:08:06,613 --> 00:08:07,530
Who?

161
00:08:07,614 --> 00:08:09,616
- Jonathan Revolution. Yeah.
- Come on.

162
00:08:09,699 --> 00:08:12,744
Johnny Rev offered me to head up
their beer and spirits division.

163
00:08:12,827 --> 00:08:14,162
- What?
- Yeah. [chuckles]

164
00:08:14,246 --> 00:08:16,039
You had a physical altercation with him.

165
00:08:16,122 --> 00:08:20,293
He must fight a lot of motherfuckers, 'cause it did not seem to negatively impact his view of me.

166
00:08:20,794 --> 00:08:27,300
- I-It's insane.
- [chuckling] I'm not taking the job, for the record, but… - Vroom, vroom. - Vroom, vroom is right.

167
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:39,938
Whoa. Did you see something?

168
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:47,486
Uh, if I'm being honest, - I'm kinda afraid to say what I just saw. - [chuckles] Was that, like, an army helicopter, - or a drone or something? - No.

169
00:08:47,529 --> 00:08:50,448
Army helicopters and drones
do not move like that.

170
00:08:50,991 --> 00:08:52,534
Was it something from Caltech?

171
00:08:52,617 --> 00:08:53,785
That was a fucking UFO.

172
00:08:53,868 --> 00:08:56,037
- Come on. No, it wasn't. Was it?
- We just saw a UFO.

173
00:08:56,121 --> 00:08:57,080
That was a UF...

174
00:08:57,163 --> 00:08:59,499
- What? Come on!
- We just saw a UFO.

175
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,626
We totally did.
Is-Is there a meteor shower tonight?

176
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:04,294
[stammers] I give you the impression
that I follow meteor showers?

177
00:09:04,337 --> 00:09:05,714
- No. [stammering]
- No.

178
00:09:05,797 --> 00:09:07,714
I really think that was a fucking UFO.
[stammering]

179
00:09:07,757 --> 00:09:10,425
Why are you taking it out?
It's already blasted off into hyperspace.

180
00:09:10,468 --> 00:09:11,595
This is like... [stammers]

181
00:09:11,678 --> 00:09:13,680
How are these words coming out
of my mouth? I...

182
00:09:13,763 --> 00:09:16,516
- That was a fucking UFO.
- Oh, my God. [whispers] We saw a UFO.

183
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,225
- We saw a fucking UFO.
- What else could it be?

184
00:09:18,268 --> 00:09:23,231
That... We just saw a UFO.
That was fully a UFO. [stammering]

185
00:09:23,315 --> 00:09:25,816
- I never thought I would see a UFO.
- I never thought I'd see one either.

186
00:09:25,859 --> 00:09:28,778
- I never even think about UFOs.
- I didn't think they were real things!

187
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:34,868
We just saw a UFO.

188
00:09:36,578 --> 00:09:38,258
- [chuckling] I can't believe it.
- We did.

189
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:40,080
What are you talking about?

190
00:09:40,123 --> 00:09:45,420
- We saw a UFO!
- I am talking about the UFO that was just above our house two minutes ago, right up there.

191
00:09:45,503 --> 00:09:47,297
- Oh, my God.
- Did you see it?

192
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:48,715
No, I don't believe in aliens.

193
00:09:48,798 --> 00:09:50,340
- [Will] What?
- Right. UFOs don't exist.

194
00:09:50,383 --> 00:09:51,718
And even if they did, who cares?

195
00:09:51,801 --> 00:09:53,678
- Who cares? Who cares?
- Oh, my God.

196
00:09:53,762 --> 00:09:56,097
Wait, are we under a flight path here?

197
00:09:56,181 --> 00:09:58,308
You're telling me
no one here saw this fucking UFO?

198
00:09:58,391 --> 00:10:00,352
- [chuckling] No, I don't think so.
- [Will] What?

199
00:10:00,435 --> 00:10:06,566
Not to rain on your parade,
but the likelihood that alien life exists in this universe, let alone is capable of traveling to earth, is infinitesimal.

200
00:10:06,650 --> 00:10:10,278
Uh, for starters, like, faster-than-light
travel is essentially impossible.

201
00:10:10,362 --> 00:10:11,488
- Says who?
- Says science.

202
00:10:11,571 --> 00:10:13,011
- [groans] Fuck science.
- "Science."

203
00:10:13,073 --> 00:10:14,281
[Will] Science doesn't know shit.

204
00:10:14,324 --> 00:10:15,657
- This is beyond science.
- "Science."

205
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:18,787
Okay. Let's try and be level-headed
and not, you know, jump to conclusions.

206
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:22,374
There's no conclusion. This is real.
The government is trying to cover it up.

207
00:10:22,457 --> 00:10:29,089
- It's a conspiracy. You know what I mean?
- I work for the city of Altadena and I've never seen any evidence of conspiracies.

208
00:10:29,172 --> 00:10:32,342
Oh, you think they're telling the city
of Alta-fucking-dena about this shit?

209
00:10:32,425 --> 00:10:33,843
- [Sylvia] Okay, well...
- Hell no.

210
00:10:33,927 --> 00:10:36,720
- He doesn't mean that. Okay.
- This is way above Altadena's pay grade.

211
00:10:36,763 --> 00:10:39,307
A lot of people like to fly kites
at Beeman Park.

212
00:10:39,391 --> 00:10:41,226
Maybe it was just a kite that got away.

213
00:10:41,309 --> 00:10:46,688
With all due respect, Diane,
I'm not a fucking moron who doesn't know the difference between a kite and a spaceship.

214
00:10:46,731 --> 00:10:51,944
Here's what we need to do.
We need to designate two people to get back on this roof and keep an eye out, - in case it does another pass. - Okay.

215
00:10:51,987 --> 00:10:54,906
I will go first. Who's with me? Let's go.
Polo, pink Polo? Let's go.

216
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:56,741
Okay. Well, you know, well, i-it-it-it...

217
00:10:56,825 --> 00:10:59,202
I'm scared of aliens.

218
00:10:59,286 --> 00:11:02,829
You should be.
It undoes everything we know… - [Sylvia] Okay. - …and that's scary.

219
00:11:02,872 --> 00:11:05,208
- Okay. Okay.
- It's fine, sweetie. Don't worry about it.

220
00:11:05,292 --> 00:11:07,376
[Will] Yeah. She's a child.
As a child, you gotta learn this shit.

221
00:11:07,419 --> 00:11:10,171
We might just duck out,
since it's getting close to bedtime.

222
00:11:10,255 --> 00:11:13,049
No, no. Please, please, don't go.
Don't go. Maybe it was a kite.

223
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:14,426
- What? No.
- Well, maybe.

224
00:11:14,509 --> 00:11:17,636
We don't know. You saw it before I did.
I was mostly just looking at it with you.

225
00:11:17,679 --> 00:11:20,597
I mean, we don't... [chuckles] You know,
the idea of a UFO is cool. It's like...

226
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:24,728
"UAP, unidentified aerial phenomenon."
These things are all over TikTok.

227
00:11:24,811 --> 00:11:26,146
- Yeah, it is.
- See?

228
00:11:26,229 --> 00:11:29,482
Okay. All right. Frances, enough.
L-Let's just... Let's-Let's move on.

229
00:11:29,566 --> 00:11:31,943
- [Charlie] Yeah.
- Hey, honey, have you had any dessert?

230
00:11:32,027 --> 00:11:34,821
'Cause I've got some really nice
fruit ice pops you might like.

231
00:11:34,905 --> 00:11:36,197
Yeah? Okay.

232
00:11:39,534 --> 00:11:41,286
You-You saw that shit too.

233
00:11:41,369 --> 00:11:42,662
[sighs] Please, Will.

234
00:11:42,746 --> 00:11:44,998
There's families here and little kids.
Our new neighbors.

235
00:11:45,081 --> 00:11:48,208
- I'm sorry. This is not the time.
- You throw me under the bus and make me seem like a lunatic?

236
00:11:48,251 --> 00:11:51,091
- That's your solution here?
- No, I'm asking you to just read the room.

237
00:11:51,171 --> 00:11:53,298
It's a backyard barbecue,
not an X-Files convention.

238
00:11:53,381 --> 00:11:56,218
- We saw a UFO!
- Please don't cause a scene.

239
00:11:56,301 --> 00:11:58,553
I'm not causing a scene!
The UFO's causing a scene!

240
00:11:58,637 --> 00:11:59,970
What are you talk... Just drop it!

241
00:12:00,013 --> 00:12:01,973
I can't drop it. How do you drop it?

242
00:12:02,057 --> 00:12:07,896
For all I know, while we're arguing
there's three more of them up there, trying to impart some wisdom about the environment or nuclear power, or something.

243
00:12:07,979 --> 00:12:10,731
And all you care about is your stupid,
fucking bullshit suburban party!

244
00:12:10,774 --> 00:12:12,234
Fuck you. You need to grow up.

245
00:12:12,317 --> 00:12:15,487
You think you're better than me 'cause
you've got these fucking cookie platters?

246
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:17,946
- We're the same. At least I can admit it.
- No. That is not true.

247
00:12:17,989 --> 00:12:20,657
You're pathetic and you're stuck,
and you're trying to pull me under.

248
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:25,538
You think a few thousand square feet
is gonna fix your problems? You're insane.

249
00:12:25,622 --> 00:12:27,749
- Fuck you! You don't know me.
- Oh, I know you.

250
00:12:27,832 --> 00:12:33,629
You are a miserable stay-at-home mom
who hangs out with me - to escape your boring life. - Well, you know who you are?

251
00:12:33,672 --> 00:12:36,841
You're an aging, pretentious hipster
who's bleaching their problems away.

252
00:12:36,925 --> 00:12:39,302
- You said you liked it!
- Because I felt sorry for you!

253
00:12:42,264 --> 00:12:44,516
- I never wanna see you again.
- That can be arranged.

254
00:12:47,811 --> 00:12:49,771
Goodbye, everyone.
It was a pleasure meeting you.

255
00:12:49,854 --> 00:12:54,025
Despite what that person is willing
to admit… [whispers] …we saw a UFO.

256
00:12:54,109 --> 00:12:55,235
We are not alone!

257
00:12:58,113 --> 00:12:59,739
And there was a fucking UFO up there!

258
00:13:00,448 --> 00:13:02,117
He said the F word.

259
00:13:02,617 --> 00:13:03,743
That's all he says.

260
00:13:04,661 --> 00:13:08,248
I'm so sorry I ruined the party.
It's such a bummer.

261
00:13:08,331 --> 00:13:11,334
Will and I just… [sighs]
…wind each other up.

262
00:13:11,418 --> 00:13:12,502
Why? Did something happen?

263
00:13:12,586 --> 00:13:14,838
- I didn't notice.
- [chuckles] You okay?

264
00:13:14,921 --> 00:13:16,631
Yeah. I'm all right.

265
00:13:16,715 --> 00:13:20,552
He'll cool off. You'll cool off.
It'll be fine.

266
00:13:21,136 --> 00:13:22,137
I dunno.

267
00:13:23,763 --> 00:13:25,223
[sighs] Hey, I, um...

268
00:13:26,349 --> 00:13:27,350
[sighs]

269
00:13:27,851 --> 00:13:28,852
Mm-hmm. What?

270
00:13:29,853 --> 00:13:39,905
Well, you know, I've always felt that,
mathematically, it seems unlikely that humans are the only living species in the universe and the most intelligent.

271
00:13:39,988 --> 00:13:45,076
You know, after your experience tonight, I thought maybe we could, like, investigate some of that stuff together.

272
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,495
We could take, like, a road trip out
to the desert.

273
00:13:47,579 --> 00:13:49,497
- Mm-hmm.
- It could be a new shared interest.

274
00:13:49,581 --> 00:13:55,253
I know you don't love golf.
And pickleball, it kind of fizzled out, so it could be something we could do together.

275
00:13:55,879 --> 00:13:56,880
Night, babe.

276
00:13:57,380 --> 00:14:02,177
[sighs] Just something we could…
[inhales sharply] …think about. Plan for.

277
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:04,012
- Mm-hmm.
- Night.

278
00:14:06,681 --> 00:14:08,975
[Sylvia yawns]

279
00:14:09,059 --> 00:14:12,854
You know, there's room on the balcony for,
like, a refracting telescope. Some power...

280
00:14:12,938 --> 00:14:15,607
[shushes, stammers] Quiet now.

281
00:14:16,691 --> 00:14:21,780
It's interesting
because you saw a UFO tonight, - but now you don't seem to care. - Mmm.

282
00:14:22,364 --> 00:14:23,573
[crickets chirping]

283
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:53,228
So what do you want me to do here?

284
00:14:53,311 --> 00:14:55,647
Uh, you're gonna wanna add two
to the boil.

285
00:14:55,730 --> 00:14:58,316
Two bags of Blue Razz Pop Rocks?

286
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,651
Oh, no, no, no.

287
00:15:03,905 --> 00:15:04,906
[grunts]

288
00:15:05,532 --> 00:15:06,700
Two buckets.

289
00:15:06,783 --> 00:15:10,912
Man, I love Pop Rocks, - 'cause they fight back. - Great.

290
00:15:16,084 --> 00:15:17,586
And this one's gonna be NERDs.

291
00:15:18,670 --> 00:15:21,089
How many buckets of NERDs
you want me to put in here?

292
00:15:21,172 --> 00:15:25,861
Uh… I don't know. Let's try six to start with. Does that sound good?

293
00:15:25,927 --> 00:15:28,597
No. None of this sounds good.

294
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:31,892
Yeah, well, I'm in charge, so six buckets.

295
00:15:31,975 --> 00:15:36,104
And then I'll try it
and make the final call, the way you used to do.

296
00:15:36,187 --> 00:15:38,857
And then,
maybe later you can unload the truck.

297
00:15:44,237 --> 00:15:46,364
Hey! Yo, asshole!

298
00:15:49,784 --> 00:15:50,785
[beeps]

299
00:15:53,246 --> 00:15:54,456
[person] Really, man?

300
00:15:57,042 --> 00:15:58,919
Okay, okay, okay. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

301
00:15:59,002 --> 00:16:01,003
- Look... I'm sorry.
- What the fuck is wrong with you?

302
00:16:01,046 --> 00:16:02,171
Look, I'll pay for the damage.

303
00:16:02,214 --> 00:16:04,047
- It can't be that much. Right?
- Seriously, man.

304
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:07,928
I don't know what you're angry about
in your life, but take it out on something else.

305
00:16:08,011 --> 00:16:14,851
This job is bad enough,
and I already don't get benefits since I'm technically a contractor thanks to some ballot initiative.

306
00:16:15,727 --> 00:16:17,354
Those fucking politicians, man.

307
00:16:17,437 --> 00:16:20,022
- Always, like, dipping their...
- [groans] Don't try to bond with me, man.

308
00:16:20,065 --> 00:16:21,149
That's not what this is.

309
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,817
Okay, I'm sorry. You're right.

310
00:16:22,901 --> 00:16:25,237
You, sir,
have lost your scootering privileges.

311
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:28,281
- [scooter bell dings]
- Sorry. Sorry.

312
00:16:35,038 --> 00:16:38,041
[Andy] Look, Sylvia, I am very excited
that you're planning our wedding.

313
00:16:38,124 --> 00:16:40,334
I am. But I'ma be honest with you.
I really get into the weeds.

314
00:16:40,377 --> 00:16:42,537
- He does. He really gets into the weeds.
- Yeah, I do.

315
00:16:42,587 --> 00:16:46,758
- Um, as I was saying…
- [cell phone rings] - …my plan for the... Oh. - You're taking another call?

316
00:16:46,841 --> 00:16:49,135
- Sylvia, what do you mean?
- Uh, I'll call you back. Bye.

317
00:16:50,303 --> 00:16:52,847
- Hello.
- May I please speak with Sylvia Greeves?

318
00:16:52,931 --> 00:16:57,477
- Yes, speaking.
- I'm Sydney Plemmings with Garouf & Associates in San Diego, California.

319
00:16:57,561 --> 00:17:00,814
Uh, we're looking into some complaints
against Jerry Revonsky.

320
00:17:00,897 --> 00:17:03,316
You were referred to us
as a potential victim.

321
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:06,570
Oh. Uh, I'm sorry,
but I don't know a Jerry Revonsky.

322
00:17:06,652 --> 00:17:08,905
Maybe his street name rings a bell.

323
00:17:10,156 --> 00:17:11,199
Johnny Rev.

324
00:17:13,243 --> 00:17:14,910
I knew that wasn't his real name.

325
00:17:17,706 --> 00:17:20,500
- Pretty good, right?
- Absolutely not. It's fucking disgusting.

326
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,501
It tastes like you dumped a bunch
of Pop Rocks in beer.

327
00:17:22,544 --> 00:17:24,295
Yeah, 'cause that's what happened.

328
00:17:25,796 --> 00:17:27,007
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yes.

329
00:17:27,090 --> 00:17:33,013
Are you here to insult my life choices and tell me I did not see the single most incredible thing I've ever seen in my entire life?

330
00:17:33,096 --> 00:17:34,806
No, I didn't. I came to show you this.

331
00:17:35,557 --> 00:17:39,019
- Five dollars off at Nordstrom?
- What? No, not this. This.

332
00:17:41,479 --> 00:17:42,647
[Sylvia] Hmm, right?

333
00:17:42,731 --> 00:17:44,900
Johnny Rev's past finally caught up
with him. Hmm?

334
00:17:44,983 --> 00:17:47,110
Apparently he has a long history
of sexual harassment.

335
00:17:47,193 --> 00:17:49,529
Shocking. Glad he got what he deserves.

336
00:17:49,613 --> 00:17:53,074
So, let's go down there
and get you that job they offered you.

337
00:17:53,158 --> 00:17:55,201
- I'll drive.
- No. Okay? Are you insane?

338
00:17:55,285 --> 00:17:57,662
I already called that lady Jenna.
She's the CEO now.

339
00:17:57,746 --> 00:17:59,705
- You called her?
- Yeah. The job's still available.

340
00:17:59,748 --> 00:18:01,915
She just wants you to come down
to San Diego to talk it over.

341
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:04,711
Look, there's nothing to talk
to her about, you know?

342
00:18:04,794 --> 00:18:06,670
I-I can't thrive
in that corporate environment, okay?

343
00:18:06,713 --> 00:18:10,300
Beer is beer. You were really impressed
with that place. You loved it down there.

344
00:18:10,383 --> 00:18:12,844
You're miserable here. [chuckles]
You're so miserable.

345
00:18:12,928 --> 00:18:15,597
What's the worst that could happen?
They hire you?

346
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:19,267
- Yes.
- Come on, man. What are you so afraid of?

347
00:18:19,351 --> 00:18:21,228
Just try something new. Take a risk.

348
00:18:21,311 --> 00:18:22,479
Why do you care so much?

349
00:18:23,230 --> 00:18:25,189
I was really stuck for a while,
and you called me on it.

350
00:18:25,232 --> 00:18:28,610
And I didn't want to hear it.
But you were really honest, and it helped.

351
00:18:28,693 --> 00:18:31,404
I've started planning Katie
and Andy's wedding.

352
00:18:31,488 --> 00:18:35,533
And I know that's not the biggest deal,
but, you know, maybe I can turn it into something.

353
00:18:36,493 --> 00:18:38,453
So, it's my turn to be honest with you.
You...

354
00:18:39,079 --> 00:18:40,872
Buddy, you gotta get out of this place.

355
00:18:42,499 --> 00:18:47,045
[stammers] But if you go, who's gonna unload the 500 pounds of Sour Patch Kids that just got delivered?

356
00:18:55,637 --> 00:18:56,888
[sighs]

357
00:19:10,777 --> 00:19:12,028
I'll be right back.

358
00:19:12,612 --> 00:19:13,512
Will?

359
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:18,201
Yo. I quit.

360
00:19:19,119 --> 00:19:20,120
Peace.

361
00:19:27,836 --> 00:19:32,549
By "quit," I mean I will sell you
my shares in this bar at a rate that we later negotiate with a lawyer present.

362
00:19:33,174 --> 00:19:34,175
Peace.

363
00:19:38,889 --> 00:19:41,975
Hi, uh, I'm here to see Jenna Lewis,
the CEO. [chuckles]

364
00:19:42,058 --> 00:19:43,101
And you are?

365
00:19:43,184 --> 00:19:45,228
I'm Will Zysman from Lucky Penny Brewery.

366
00:19:45,312 --> 00:19:47,898
Uh, about the job opening.
Think she's expecting me. [chuckles]

367
00:19:47,981 --> 00:19:49,983
Okay, give me one second.

368
00:19:52,652 --> 00:19:53,944
You gonna change all these signs?

369
00:19:53,987 --> 00:19:55,614
[stammers] We're working on it.

370
00:19:55,697 --> 00:19:59,117
Need new shirts and shit too.
It's like you're wearing R. Kelly merch.

371
00:20:01,828 --> 00:20:05,081
Okay, I've let her know that you're here.
So why don't you have a seat?

372
00:20:05,165 --> 00:20:06,166
Great. Thank you.

373
00:20:10,670 --> 00:20:11,570
[sighs]

374
00:20:12,589 --> 00:20:14,424
Oh, God. Here she comes. [sighs]

375
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:17,009
So, full disclosure,
I never actually talked to Jenna.

376
00:20:17,052 --> 00:20:19,469
But, uh, I did leave her a message,
and she hasn't called me back yet.

377
00:20:19,512 --> 00:20:25,101
'Cause she may or may not remember
who we are. But we're here, so… - What? What are you talking about? What? - Yeah.

378
00:20:25,185 --> 00:20:27,394
- Why did you do that?
- Because you wouldn't have come otherwise.

379
00:20:27,437 --> 00:20:28,937
We drove here for two hours for no reason?

380
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:30,981
- Oh, no. It's fine.
- Oh, my God. Let's get out of here.

381
00:20:31,024 --> 00:20:32,482
- You just get in front of her.
- Let's go.

382
00:20:32,525 --> 00:20:33,777
- Hi.
- Oh, my God. Hi.

383
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:37,321
- What are you guys doing here?
- Uh, we were just - going to the beach. - We were... We went to the zoo.

384
00:20:37,364 --> 00:20:39,004
- And I had a swim.
- And went to the zoo.

385
00:20:39,199 --> 00:20:41,243
[Will] Um, yeah. [inhales deeply]

386
00:20:43,161 --> 00:20:50,335
[clicks tongue] Last time, uh…
[chuckles] …I saw you, you mentioned that you would hire me if I was looking for a job.

387
00:20:50,418 --> 00:20:53,713
And I... I guess I'm...
I'm looking for a job.

388
00:20:53,797 --> 00:20:56,758
Uh… [chuckles] …so I don't know
if there's still any available.

389
00:20:56,841 --> 00:20:58,843
Uh, I can give you a résumé
if you want one.

390
00:20:58,927 --> 00:21:05,934
I just need a printer and 45 minutes
to write a résumé. Um… Look, this is silly. I can see you're... you're very busy here.

391
00:21:06,017 --> 00:21:07,978
Uh, I'm sorry for wasting your time.

392
00:21:08,061 --> 00:21:10,188
[stammers] Wait. Where are you guys going?

393
00:21:12,190 --> 00:21:15,443
- Congratulations. How about that?
- [chuckles] Thank you.

394
00:21:15,527 --> 00:21:18,905
- Excited?
- I am a little terrified.

395
00:21:18,989 --> 00:21:21,429
It's just... It's so different
from anything I've done before.

396
00:21:21,491 --> 00:21:24,244
You're gonna create
so many drinks I won't like.

397
00:21:24,327 --> 00:21:26,705
I'll make one just for you.
I'll call it the Sylvia.

398
00:21:26,788 --> 00:21:31,877
It'll be Riesling with apple juice,
a Sun Chip rim, served in a full-size toddler's car seat.

399
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,546
- I would drink the crap out of that.
- You would.

400
00:21:34,629 --> 00:21:36,214
[both chuckle]

401
00:21:36,298 --> 00:21:39,634
I can't believe I have to drive
to and from San Diego for work every day.

402
00:21:40,427 --> 00:21:44,097
Yeah, but if you take the job, you're...
you're gonna have to move to San Diego.

403
00:21:46,892 --> 00:21:50,145
I honestly didn't think
about that at all. Wow.

404
00:21:54,107 --> 00:21:58,737
You're gonna be so good at that job.
And a change is always really good.

405
00:22:00,238 --> 00:22:01,907
And what's keeping you in LA?

406
00:22:09,664 --> 00:22:10,790
You guys want flowers?

407
00:22:10,874 --> 00:22:12,834
No. We're, uh... We're not together.

408
00:22:12,918 --> 00:22:15,962
I'm married to somebody else.
He's not... He's not here.

409
00:22:16,046 --> 00:22:17,756
Much more handsome guy.

410
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,257
You want flowers?

411
00:22:20,091 --> 00:22:22,510
You know what? I do want a flower.

412
00:22:22,594 --> 00:22:24,846
Thank you so much.
Your pitch worked. [chuckles]

413
00:22:24,930 --> 00:22:26,640
[Sylvia laughs] Aw.

414
00:22:26,723 --> 00:22:29,809
- Thank you, sir. Thank you.
- Thanks so much.

415
00:22:31,102 --> 00:22:33,355
- For you, my lady.
- Well, thank you.

416
00:22:33,897 --> 00:22:36,483
It's very fake. Very plastic. [chuckles]

417
00:22:37,275 --> 00:22:38,777
That means it will last forever.

418
00:23:08,557 --> 00:23:10,934
Oh, could you pick up Simon
from soccer on Saturday?

419
00:23:11,017 --> 00:23:16,146
Ah, sorry, babe.
I have the Schaeffer twins' bat mitzvah, and the following weekend I have that baby shower in Palm Springs.

420
00:23:16,189 --> 00:23:18,316
But I could do the next weekend.

421
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,440
- Yeah? Soccer run?
- Yeah.

422
00:23:19,901 --> 00:23:22,653
Okay, I gotta go, - I gotta get there before the caterers. - Pick a tie.

423
00:23:22,696 --> 00:23:24,364
- Uh, this one.
- Great, okay. Bye.

424
00:23:24,447 --> 00:23:26,032
- Bye.
- Who are we sitting with?

425
00:23:26,116 --> 00:23:28,577
Katie's family,
and Will's coming in from San Diego.

426
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:30,745
- Will. Wow. It's been a while.
- Yeah. I know.

427
00:23:30,829 --> 00:23:32,455
I know. It'll be really good to see him.

428
00:23:33,081 --> 00:23:34,666
- Okay. I'll see you there.
- Bye.

429
00:23:49,055 --> 00:23:51,057
["Canon in D Major" playing]

430
00:23:56,271 --> 00:23:57,314
[Omar] Sylvia. [chuckles]

431
00:23:58,231 --> 00:24:01,109
